Open terminal of your choosing.
Create a script called script.sh with the following content:
#!/bin/bash

sleep 5m

Make the script executable and run it in background using command script.sh &
Verify that your script is running in the background using jobs command.
Inspect running processes in you sytem using top and ps commands.
Find the PID of your script.
Find command and user infrormation about your script.
Self-review:

The script is running.
You are able to determine script's PID, user and command information.
